Y = -X + 1
EY
 E(Y) = E(-X + 1) = -E(X) + 1 
Y=g(X)=-X+1
 \begin{align*} E(Y)&=E(g(X))\\ &=\int_{-\infty}^\infty g(x)f(x)dx\\ &=\int_{-\infty}^\infty(-x+1)f(x)dx\\ &=-\int_{-\infty}^\infty xf(x)dx + \int_{-\infty}^\infty f(x)dx\\ &=-E(X) + 1 \end{align*}
